# Main KV file - loaded automatically by Kivy based on the App class name (MoneyTrackerApp -> moneytracker.kv)
# Can define global styles or rules if necessary.
# ScreenManager is now created in main.py, so this file can be minimal or empty
# unless you want to define styles applicable to all screens/widgets.

# Example global styles (optional):
# <Label>:
#     font_name: 'Roboto' # Set default font if Roboto is available

# <Button>:
#     font_name: 'Roboto'
#     border: (dp(2), dp(2), dp(2), dp(2)) # Example border for all buttons